## PART 4: CUI HANDLING REQUIREMENTS

### Authority: DoDI 5200.48; 32 CFR Part 2002

If any CUI is present in the system, ALL of the following requirements apply.

Requirement 4.1 - Marking:
Per DoDI 5200.48, Section 3.4 and 32 CFR Part 2002.20: CUI must be marked with the CUI designation at the time of creation. Headers, footers, and portion marks are required on all documents containing CUI.

Requirement 4.2 - Splash Screen:
Per DoDI 5200.48, Section 3.4(d): “For systems, networks, and programs operating on the various domains, a splash screen warning and notice of consent must be employed to alert users of CUI within the program.”

- The splash screen must appear before any CUI is displayed.
- Users must affirmatively acknowledge the warning.
- The acknowledgment must be logged.

Requirement 4.3 - Dissemination Controls:
Per 32 CFR Part 2002.16: CUI dissemination is limited to individuals with a lawful government purpose and a need to know. The system must enforce this at the access control layer.

Requirement 4.4 - Non-DoD System Requirements:
Per DoDI 5200.48, Section 3.4(c): “Non-DoD information systems processing, storing, or transmitting CUI will provide adequate security, and the appropriate requirements must be incorporated into all contracts, grants, and other legal agreements with non-DoD entities in accordance with DoDI 8582.01. The NIST SP 800-171 governs and protects CUI on non-Federal IS when applied by contract.”

Per DoDI 5200.48, Section 3.4(b): DoD personnel will NOT use personal email accounts, personal messaging systems, or other non-DoD information systems (except approved or authorized government contractor systems) to conduct official business involving CUI.

Requirement 4.5 - Unauthorized Disclosure Reporting:
Per DoDI 5200.48, Section 3.5(a)(4): Misuse, mishandling, or unauthorized disclosure of CUI must be reported to the Unauthorized Disclosure Program Management Office and the appropriate Military Department Counterintelligence Organization.

**PoC EXCEPTION:** If a qualified authority (e.g., Battle Captain, Security Officer) makes an on-record determination that no actual CUI is present in the system, document that determination in writing, preserve the documentation, and use it as the baseline for all subsequent CUI analysis. Do not file a spillage report for content that was officially determined to contain no CUI.

