## PART 8: MANDATORY DISCLAIMERS AND LABELING FOR PoC SYSTEMS

Every PoC application must display the following in a visible location on every page or interface:

REQUIRED LABEL:
“PROOF OF CONCEPT - NOT AN OPERATIONAL SYSTEM. This application is not authorized for use with actual Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI) or Personally Identifiable Information (PII). All data used in this system must be synthetic or anonymized. Unauthorized use of real government data in this system constitutes a violation of DoDI 5200.48 and DoDI 5400.11.”

If any CUI will be present, add the required DoD splash screen per DoDI 5200.48 Section 3.4(d):
“WARNING: This system processes Controlled Unclassified Information (CUI). Access is restricted to individuals with a lawful government purpose and a documented need to know. By proceeding, you acknowledge and consent to all conditions of the Standard Mandatory Notice and Consent Provision.”

