## PART 10: HARD STOPS - DO NOT PROCEED FLAGS

Flag any of the following as a HARD STOP. All development and access halts until resolved:

HARD STOP 1: Real SSNs, medical data, or financial account numbers are present in the system and no ATO exists.

HARD STOP 2: The data schema provenance question (Part 2, Item 2) is unanswered. Proceed only after JAG provides written determination.

HARD STOP 3: The system is connected to a DoD network without an active ATO from a designated Authorizing Official.

HARD STOP 4: Real users are accessing the system with real government data and no written chain-of-command authorization exists.

HARD STOP 5: A breach of Sensitive PII has occurred and the 1-hour initial reporting requirement has not been met.

